post_text:
The Wildcats would like to welcome Coach Austin Guinn(pictured on the left with wife Sydney) and Coach Jordynn Terry(pictured on right with husband and new boys coach, Devin Terry).
Coach Guinn takes over the Lady Wildcats basketball program after finishing the year as the head Byng Boys Basketball coach. Originally from Okemah, Coach Guinn played his college basketball at OBU before finishing his degree at ECU.
Coach Terry takes over the fastpitch and slowpitch programs after a stellar career at ECU, where she is the schools all time leader in homeruns, RBI’s, and total bases. She was recently named to the GAC conference all decade team.
Welcome to Earlsboro!!

Starting Monday, March 23, from 10am to 12 noon each missed school day, we will be giving out breakfast and lunch, at the same time, through our nutrition provider, Keystone. post_text: Sharilee Strickland & Katelyn Martin represented the Arbuckle Federal Credit Union today at Earlsboro Schools. They, along with the help of the Latta DECA club, Communications Credit Union employees and 3 other helpers, held a Financial Reality Fair for our 9th-12th graders. This taught them how to budget their monthly expenses and adjust their "wants & needs" accordingly to actually be able to afford them, which may I say was quite entertaining 🤣 I would definitely recommend every high school hosting one for their students.

Dillon Atkinson
March 7, 2019 at 9:50 PM ·

Tonight was one of those nights that really made me love what I do. During our game against Sasakwa, we learned that one of their players is having surgery tomorrow and tonight would be his last game of his career. One of our seniors, Chance Bohannon, decided the team was going to give him a game ball that the team signed to let him know he was in our thoughts and prayers. Wins and losses aside, a team filled with this kind of character will always be a champion.

post_text:
Senior Pie in the Face Auction Example!!!

This is where I got the idea to start our annual senior pie in the face auction. This school does it every year, and it is 1 of the 2 biggest fundraisers that the seniors hold. I recorded quite a few examples. This specific 1 raised $400. I believe the lowest that I recorded was for $150. The sheriff's daughter raised $1,000 by herself, but I didn't get it recorded. I just want family and friends as well as seniors and future seniors to see how successful this fundraiser can be when everyone comes together, not to mention how fun it is getting to pie them in the face 😁😁😁

post_text: We are opening this up to the public. Everyone is welcome! I know how important blood donors were to Chad's treatments so that he could receive his blood transfusions. With this in mind, I ask you to become a blood donor in his memory. Chad did anything and everything to help and support others, so may we show our love for him by helping save the lives of those in need.
